post.body:
- we review zero plans;
- we invite the most promising zero-starters and discuss;
- as much as possible we make our discussions, investment intentions, and actual investment open for examinations of the zero community;
- we invest, and typically we look to own 20% of the startup we make investment in;
- we follow their progresses, and report them here;
- we promote our startups;
- we raise more fund from bigger VCs for our zero-startups;
- we push either for their IPO, or other cashout events;

Hey, this is a great time to join the great zero revolution. Let us here from you, there are many projects waiting for a great guy like you. Here is a list of things we are thinking of doing - 

- zero chat: by far we think there is a great need here; let's beat the hell out of things like wechat and so on;
- zeromail extension: making zeromail working with regular .com emails;
- zero game: it becomes almost boring now without some zero games;
- z-commerce;
- search engine for zites;
- zero antivirus;
